President Trump delivered remarks on healthcare during a visit to North Carolina. He outlined his vision for a healthcare system that puts patients first, families first, and America first. He discussed his America First Healthcare Plan, which aims to ensure high-quality care, affordable insurance options, lower prescription drug costs, price transparency, and protection for patients with preexisting conditions. He criticized the Democratic Party's healthcare plans as socialist and claimed they would lead to rationed care, limited choices, and delayed access to lifesaving treatments. The President also highlighted his administration's efforts to combat the COVID-19 pandemic, including the development of vaccines through Operation Warp Speed. He emphasized his commitment to protecting Medicare and implementing reforms to improve access and affordability for American patients. The President signed an executive order to implement his healthcare agenda and protect patients with preexisting conditions.